The paper deals with the problem of generalized flow maximization, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper are related to graph algorithms, linear programming, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
